            "answer_text": "The original question is \u201cCan a scientist invent things?\u201d Modern science is based on incorrect and incomplete concepts of a mechanical universe of physical atoms. They have spent a lot of time and money \u201cproving\u201d the standard model of particle physics and a universe that is not founded in intelligence, consciousness,love and light. Without the correct fundamental concepts, scientists tend to measure and calculate things rather than invent new things that are good for the whole. To answer the above, modified question, they don\u2019t invent anything new. They innovate, based on laws of physics and assumptions that are held within the same channels of their consciousness by limiting concepts. ",
